An anniversary was founded in 1397 by Hugh Wallace of Oraigie, for himself, and his parents and. successors, and an annual grant of four bolls of white oat meal, or in default thereos forty pence for each boll, was secured on the granter's lands of Oraigie.⁷ This was confirmed in 1419ss and 1480 ⁹ by his successors.
